The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Committees will set up a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the Monday strike that will last for an indefinite time.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the unemployment will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since rail traffic will be completely stopped and until 13 hours the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon the League Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike they will hold jointly with the National Federation of Workers' Committees.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Machinery Union will also be set up to coordinate the actions of Monday.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating trade unions will pronounce themselves on strike for indefinite time, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the Public Health Act, the trade unions shall immediately withdraw their appeal to strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on at very late hours of the night, or perhaps at midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: in the railways we will stop working for an indefinite time, in the morning we may stop a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the interurban bus transport of Volan companies.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some trade unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for defined time.
Until Thursday afternoon the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement on even the minimum services, although, as Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 13 hours the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, the Budapest Airports from 7:00 to 9:00 a.m., will hold a four-hour strike by the LIGA Trade Unions of Electrical and thermal energy industry, the Educational Unions called for a 2-hour strike and the Democratic Union of Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Medical Association will take a national strike at alternative hours and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS) which are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and put a new conception into a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of calculation of pensions that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, for advanced pensions, that occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Rail Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the side lines of the railway and expect another proposal different.
Political Capital[b1]: The Hungarian Guard's risk is increased in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysing Division) of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Better Hungary Movement, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from a number of points of view.
The company's "risk warning" writes: in relation to the Hungarian Guard's activity, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic clashes can occur."
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They affirmed that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate on the Gypsy problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, prevents normal dialogue, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "were significantly deteriorating the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of the country's stability and democratic development".
We are reminded that since the autumn of 2006, the reorganization of the radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has been increasingly publicized and promoted and that since the summer of 2007, many organizations have been formed in the country that are self-defenced by "national self-defence associations".
"The common trait of these groups is that they self-defense themselves as civil organizations, while they openly proclaim the training of their members for defence - even armed - (civil defense, national defence, defence of public order), referring to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, that is, the State," they add.
