Automobile insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, is an important expenditure that will depend on various factors such as age, sex, seniority of the card, civil status, type of vehicle to be secured or used, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is entered into in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for taking responsibility for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account a number of factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, civil status, the type of vehicle to be secured or the use of it, among others.
Insurers set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that more likely to suffer an accident, more cost to be paid.
That is why both women and older than 25 have to pay lower premiums, as statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of sinisterity due to their prudence.
Also, by taking the counts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the likelihood of having some kind of percance.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
That is why the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 are in a variety of disadvantages when hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as the limited driving experience and the old age of the card.
Although the ideal to be well-insured is a safe at all risk, there are other more economic options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a whole risk with franchise, so that they get insurance coverage at all risk but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would mean that the customer pays part of the amount of the loss.
"The portion of the amount of the loss provided by the client will be preset according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," explains Luis Noguera, the highest responsible in Spain of First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is guaranteed protection from damage caused to third-party, but not to those caused in his own car.
Besides, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A tip.
If you are under 25 try to be careful and avoid the accidents as far as possible, as this will have an impact on the bonus, which can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction over the company's base rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that basic fee.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the profit of the company.
If the company has had a good year it will be possible to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After the 25-year-old strip drivers have it easier to hire a insurance, as the sinisterity index is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to take a full risk with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when using an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of driving, after the last time the 'novice'.
However, if the client is married but still has no children it is preferable that he negotiates a insurance at all risk, provided that his economic situation permits him, of course.
Marriage with children, for their part, is considered by insurers as the public with a lower rate of sinisterity, so the surcharge will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with franchise (which may be EUR 300), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of vehicle life.
"They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford themselves the luxury of assuming a greater amount of franchise," Luis Noguera judgment.
For retirees, insurance at all risk is recommended with franchise (which is EUR 150), or one extended to third parties when a high level of bonus is available.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to adequately study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
